    "summary": "- 20 years practical experience in Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH) services delivery and water resources management, in rural and urban contexts across Africa, Asia and Latin America with a focus on sustainability and systems solutions.\n\n- current focus on building partnerships with political influence, scaling training through the WASH systems academy and supporting decentralisation within IRCs network.\n\n- established IRCs Ethiopia Country Programme, \n\n- management experience of complex multi-annual and multi-partner work-packages, projects and programmes with budgets of up to 1.2 million Euros. \n\n- previous roles at IRC have included managing the innovation-focused International Programme, co-organising international symposia (on accountability and monitoring topics), and coordinating themes on Integrated Water Resources Management and  transparency and accountability.\n\n- experience organising events and in the commissioning and delivery of research and knowledge products of all kinds including books, guidelines, training packages, briefing notes, journal special issues etc\n\n- member of Rural Water Supply Network core group on Self-supply, previously served on international steering committee of the Water Integrity Network, as secretary and chair of the Multiple Use water Services group and as member and chair of IRCs works council. Also represented IRC within the International NGO charter and prepared IRC reports on accountability.",
